# 7. Core Schemas

## Shot

Represents one camera sequence.

Fields:

```
shot_id

scene_id

duration

camera_type

camera_motion

location

characters

combat_event

visual_description

animation_directive

effects

```

---

## Scene

Represents a cinematic segment.

Fields:

```
scene_id

title

purpose

start_move

end_move

duration

shots

```

---

## CinematicSequence

Represents the complete movie blueprint.

Fields:

```
sequence_id

battle_metadata

duration

scenes

```

---

# 8. Cinematic Decision Logic

The engine uses priority scoring.

Priority:

```
Finishing Strike
        |
        v
Major Tactical Event
        |
        v
Sacrifice
        |
        v
Breakthrough Attack
        |
        v
Checks
        |
        v
Strategic Movement
```

High priority events receive:

- dedicated shots
- close cameras
- longer duration
- stronger effects

